items.name: Pony Diffusion
items.description:
>> CHECK OUT PONY DIFFUSION V5 <<

Pony Diffusion is a Stable Diffusion model that has been fine-tuned on high-quality pony, furry and other non photorealistic SFW and NSFW images.

This model is capable of producing SFW and NSFW content so it's recommended to use 'safe' prompt in combination with negative prompt for features you may want to suppress (i.e. nudity) if you want to avoid NSFW outputs.

Despite its name, this model is capable of producing wide range of furry and cartoon images as side effect of improving data diversity (with exception of anime styles, for which Waifu Diffusion is much stronger choice).

Join our Discord Server to get access to new versions of this model and free Stable Diffusion bot.

Special thanks to Waifu-Diffusion for providing finetuning expertise and advising through the process, without their help this project would not exist.

items.name: [Umi AI] Macross v2
items.description:
Umi AI is a premier replacement mod for Wildcards that many people have been using since they first appeared in October 2022. Umi AI is not only an incredible extension for rapidly generating randomized prompts of all sorts of people, creatures, and settings, but it is now also an Embedding Repository with organized and credited embeds from across the internet. Join the Umi Discord today!

This model release for Umi AI is split into three sub-models. Each model is general-purpose and good at most things, but they are also specifically tailored for certain requirements:

Divine Macross the v2 update: Generate awesome anime characters in a huge variety of styles. This model is an extremely robust general purpose anime model, made even better if you upscale while using the Remacri Upscaler! (Place Remacri inside stable-diffusion-webui\models\ESRGAN and reload WebUI)

Olympus Landscapes: A model that generates extremely high quality landscapes, space battles, and fantasy settings. It can also generate very high quality anime characters, though that is not its primary purpose.
(Version 1 can be found here: https://civitai.com/models/6077/umi-ai-mythology-and-babes-by-dutchalex)

This model will be getting a v2 update within the next few days and should see solid improvements.

Aphrodite Realgirls: A model that generates extremely lifelike human women, but also men as well. It can do SFW and NSFW alike, and it is extremely flexible in how you can prompt it!
(Version 1 can be found here: https://civitai.com/models/6077/umi-ai-mythology-and-babes-by-dutchalex)

This model will also be getting a v2 update within the next few days and should see solid improvements.

What makes these models so special? Well, I'm glad you asked. No longer do you need to add Masterpiece, High Quality, or other such things to your prompts. Now, you can much more easily change the style of an output. UmiAI comes with wildcards tested on and designed for all these models, and notably they work really well with the different artstyles Umi can produce. Even Aphrodite can often generate anime-styling well!

For more info, check out the Umi AI page where you can find install instructions here:

https://www.patreon.com/posts/umi-ai-official-73544634

If you want to learn how to better improve your promptcrafting, join the Umi AI Discord today! This also helps Umi AI become the best possible system for generating prompts and making characters come to life! We'd also love to see what you come up with as well!

items.name: Konami Kirie (World Trigger) Character LoRA
items.description:
Konami Kirie Character LoRA

If you enjoy my models and want to support me you could buy me a coffee!

This LoRA mimics the character Konami Kirie from World Trigger.

The example images were created with NeverEndingDream and AbyssOrangeMix2_sfw on 0.85 weight but feel free to experiment on your own. I tried briefly to mix it with a couple of different embeddings and it gave back decent results but you might find a better way to mix them (changing different weights etc.).

To change the weight just change the '1' in this prompt: <lora:konami-Kirie-LoRA:1>.

I'd love to see the art you guys make with it so feel free to add them in comments.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Fey (Fandeltales) - Derpixon Character
items.description:
LoRA for the character Fey from Derpixon's Fandeltales video.

Many won't know who this is but I'm sharing for those who do, or care. It turned out well I think. I trained it with 74 screencaps I took and edited at 19 epochs with a dim/alpha of 64/32.

Notes:

  • My experience has shown scale 0.5 ~ 0.8 works best, but my best results were 0.58. It gets more "cartoony" at higher scales, it looks good but the linework becomes bad; play around with it.

  • My prompt order shown in the sample pictures worked best for me.

  • To trigger the character "Fey" I reliably called the following after the loRA : "Fey_Fandeltales , green hair bow, bangs, 1girl, solo, orange eyes,blonde hair, long hair, (armor, ponytail, shoulder pads) , parted bangs, small breasts". Add clothing descriptions to negatives to generate alternate outfits; refer to pictures.

  • Not intended, but this can be used to get a Derpixon style if you ignore the above bullet point and instead describe what you want or even place a different character textual inversion. Refer to the last two pictures.

  • I used FoxyaNSFW model, but this should work with others.

  • Doesn't seem to play well with certain other LoRAs, it could be this LoRA's fault or the other ones I was using, but textual inversions are good.

  • Refer to my pictures for examples and what upscaler I used, keep in mind I have used other textual inversions to help with poses and negatives.

  • Meant for nsfw so if you want to use this for sfw, remember to put nsfw in negative prompts etc.

  • Even if you don't use it for the character, I happen to like the aesthetics regarding colour, outlines etc so it can be nice to play around with. If so: add, "green hair bow, bangs, orange eyes, blonde hair, long hair, (armor, ponytail, shoulder pads), parted bangs, small breasts " to negatives.

  • Kohya LoRA trainer that I used for training, link.

items.name: Harem dancer
items.description:
This LoRA can generate Harem outfit, Dancer, as well as face veil (mouth veil) and see-through clothes.

The training data for harem outfits are more revealing, while dancers are more gorgeous, but the actually generated results may vary.

To generate face veil, both Face veil and Mouth veil can be used, both are effective and can be switched depending on the situation.

Due to the training results of the LoRA, almost anything that is wrapped around the mouth will become transparent, so prompts such as mask may also be affected, maybe they can help generate face veils.

There may be some issues when generating head veil probably because its keyword has been taken.

Face veils are the main focus of this LoRA, but it is more difficult than expected, and there are still many problems with the generating.

If needed, this LoRA can also be used on male characters.

Note: standing_on_one_leg can solve some anatomical issues when dancing.
Useful prompts: ornate, intricate, water, light particles, glitters, shiny, belly chain, anklet, dress, wind

items.name: Artificer - Risk of Rain
items.description:
The Artificer*! This lora can be yours for the low price of 10 lunar coins...

This is a lora trained on 120 hand picked images of the Artificer from Risk of Rain 2. It was mostly trained on digital art, but there is a smidgeon of 3d art to assist. It gets the helmet pretty good, however it seems really biased against her wearing her usual outfit... See notes below for more info. It was trained on danbooru-style tags, so use those when trying to prompt - I've included the tags in a .txt file in the "Training Images" download below.

It works pretty well with most ckpts, but I recommend Anything 4.5, I used it for all of the example images.

NOTES:

-It seems quite biased to give the Artificer wide hips unprompted, and also she doesn't like wearing her usual tabard-thing. Also, the AI seems to think her black bodysuit is her actual skin, so expect some oddities from that. Tags: pelvic_curtain & tabard -- will help her wear her usual outfit... usually.

-You can pretty easily make the helmet "blush" if you add relevant tags.

-It can generate "male" versions of Artificer if you prompt it correctly.

Example prompt: (See example images, all images should still have their metadata. Just drag the images onto the PNG info tab and import it.)

Check out my Huntress model here: https://civitai.com/models/20542/huntress-risk-of-rain

items.name: Karulawaturei (Karura) - Utawarerumono
items.description:
Karura is the best catgirl period. Dissident opinions will be ignored. One might argue that she is not strictly a catgirl but a tigergirl or some other feline but she would still be the best felinegirl so the point is moot.

Seems to work fine between .4 to .8ish.

Had good results with: <lora:Karulawaturei:.7>, karulawaturei, big_breasts, collar, chain

Using metal_collar instead of collar changes the style somewhat in an interesting but subtle way. There are a couple images in her training dataset in which she has her hair free, I haven't experimented with that but to keep her hair stable you might wish to add the braid tag.

Warning: Avoid using the tail or cat_tail tag, it seems to like to fuse it with her braid causing abominations.

I have added the tag summary in place of the training data as i had to use some screen captures from the tv series and game and i am a bit uncomfortable uploading stuff that is not fanart.

items.description:
I know, there's already a Samus LoRA. Well here's another one!

Using <lora:samus:0.5> seems to be the sweet spot.
Her mole is hit or miss but, if you bump <lora:samus:#> up to 0.6 or 0.7, it shows up more consistently; at the cost of slightly less defined lips and eyes.

Share what you make! I'd love to see it!

You can get some pretty realistic looking results, depending on your tags (obviously). Also, the Zero Suit seems to render accurately in most of my testing. Just use the (zero suit) tag.

Her Paralyzer gun was in the training data. Using (gun) gets you in the ballpark, but I just can't seem to get weapons to render accurately. You may have better luck with some experimentation.

Due to the lack of P5 LoRA featuring boys (except Joker), I decided to make one for Akechi Goro.

Winter Uniform

akechi gorou, winter uniform, 1boy, solo, striped necktie, black gloves, black pants, black loafers

Summer Uniform

items.name: Amatsukaze and Shimakaze
items.description:
Amatsukaze, Shimakaze, and a joint Amatsukaze Shimakaze LoRA. The joint LoRA on its own only has like 10% chance of generating 2girls without mixing outfit, but since it's a single LoRA it works great with Latent Couple without the usual issues of combining character LoRA, or the frying from Composable LoRA.

Trained tags are:

- amatsukaze, brown sailor dress, amatsuthighhighs, smokestack hair ornament, garter straps, side-tie panties, see-through, single glove, choker, rudder shoes, rensouhou-kun, rigging, torpedo tubes

- shimakaze, cropped serafuku, shimathighhighs, white elbow gloves, blue miniskirt, black highleg panties, anchor hair ornament, rensouhou-chan, rudder boots, rigging, torpedo tubes

Many of the keywords are optional. Anchor hair ornament, rudder shoes, rudder boots, etc.

Rensouhou-chan, Rensouhou-kun, rigging, torpedo tubes tend to generate machine horrors, unfortunately. Consider actually putting them into the negative prompt.

items.name: WAS's ComfyUI Workspaces (HR-Fix and more!)
items.description:
These are worksapces to load into ComfyUI for various tasks such as HR-Fix with AI Model Upscaling

Note: WAS's Comprehensive Node Suite (WAS Node Suite) has a bloom filter now which works similar, except provides a high frequency pass to base the bloom off of. This is more accurate and used in screen-space bloom like in video games.

Requirements:

  • HR-Fix Bloom Workspace depends on Filters Suite V3, and NSP CLIPTextEncode nodes from here: https://civitai.com/models/20793/was-node-suites-comfyui

HR-Fix Usage:

  1. Extract "ComfyUI-HR-Fix_workspace.json" (or whatever the worksapce is called)

  2. Load workspace with the "Load" button in the right-hand menu and select "ComfyUI-HR-Fix_workspace.json"

  3. Select your desired diffusion model

  4. Select VAE model or use diffusion models vae

  5. Select your desired upscale model

  6. change prompt and sampling settings as seen fit.
    (currently v1 set to 512x768 x4= 2048x3072, v2 has a resize so final size is 1024x1536)

items.name: SingleLineArt Style LoRA
items.description:
This model is best suited for generating portraits of faces, though it can do full body renders as well albeit with less accuracy as far as the single line art style is concerned.

It also works well with ControlNet using depth and openpose.

When you use this LoRA in Txt2IMG, it will attempt to inject some colour and shading into your image. If you don't want colour or shading in your images, you can either :

  • Use negative prompts and add terms like "colour", "shading" to try to reduce or remove those effects from your images.

  • Use positive prompts such as "monochrome", "B&W", "flat colour", "simple", "minimalistic"

As an alternative workflow for simpler B&W images, use the LoRA in the IMG2IMG using the following steps :

  1. Load a plain white 512x512 square as your base image

  2. Set the denoising to 0.9

  3. Invoke your prompt and ensure to call the LoRA, eg. SingleLineArt style B&W line drawing of a yoga instructor in a pose<lora:SingleLineArt-LORA:1>

  4. For a hand-drawn on paper look, substitute the blank white image from step 1 for a scanned paper texture and set your denoising to 0.7 - 0.9

LoRA extractions is not as good as the full model but it creates a compromise between size and quality and it can be used along other LoRA model with a full model. Credit goes the creator of the checkpoint in version description

Please provide request link(s) in my comments "Suggestions for a model extraction?"

04.0417.23 Name version is limited to 10 25 character, make it impossible to see full name... see below "List of all LoRA model".

How to use it in AUTOMATIC1111 WebUI?

  • Place the LoRA model in .\stable-diffusion-webui\models\Lora then use <lora:filename:multiplier> in the prompt.

About the comparison:

  • Picture order: First = LoRA, Second = Fine-tuned Model, Third = Base Model

  • DM = Network Dimension ( 120=lower quality/low size, 320=higher quality/higher size ) same for CD = Conv Dimension (Rank)
    [CD is optionally if you wish to use it, install the extension: https://github.com/KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-locon (How? Extensions -> Install from URL)]
    Obviously Version "1024CV1024" or in short "1024" use more VRAM
    I did a large comparison DM+CV here

  • sample pictures does not use vea and LoRA model with SDv1.4

  • every model from (Stable Diffusion Base Model: mostly sd-v1-4.ckpt, model base is determined by highest % affinity) was extracted using Kohya_ss (Save precision: fp16)

  • Name format: <Type><DM> <CV><Name>
